      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PURO (5) was out of the money when resuming from a spell last start over 1200m at Port Hedland. Has a fair record when second up, including two top-three finishes. Fitter so anticipating a better run this time. HEZAZEB (1) showed good early speed from the inside draw last time and stalked the lead before fading to finish fourth over 1300m at Port Hedland. Well placed and expected to feature. WARBY RANGES (2) has been out of the placings in two runs since a break, the latest when sixth over 1300m at Port Hedland after he travelled towards the rear of the field. Has further improvement to come and is expected to run well. FRIES WITH THAT (6) is returning from a spell of seven months. Finished 16th at Northam over 1400m at the first run last prep. Now with a new trainer Michael Ball. Can make an impression on resumption.",
